## ‚ùå Why Monitoring Fails in Zero Trust Setups

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Too Many Signals, Zero Meaning

Zero Trust explodes telemetry:

- Auth logs  
- Network flows  
- API calls  
- Endpoint events  
- Cloud audit trails  

Teams drown in data and call it security.  
Noise wins. Signal suffocates.

More logs ‚â† more awareness.  
It usually means less.

---

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Alerts Are Tuned for Compliance, Not Attackers

Most alerts fire on:

- Login failures  
- Policy violations  
- Static thresholds  

Attackers don‚Äôt trip those. They:

- Use valid credentials  
- Stay under limits  
- Move slowly  

Your SIEM celebrates silence  
while the house empties.

