## üß® The Ugly Truth

Zero Trust doesn‚Äôt fail at **prevention**.  
It fails at **decisive reaction**.

If your system can‚Äôt:

- Instantly revoke tokens  
- Kill active sessions  
- Isolate identities  
- Lock down blast radius  

Then monitoring is just **historical documentation of your loss**.

---

## ‚úÖ What Actually Helps (And Yes, It‚Äôs Painful)

- Fewer alerts, brutally curated  
- Behavioral baselines **per identity**  
- Automatic response for high-confidence abuse  
- Session-level kill switches  
- Assume alerts are real until proven otherwise  

False positives are annoying.  
False negatives are catastrophic.

---

## üß† Final Reality Check

Logging everything is easy.  
Watching the *right* things and acting fast is hard.

If nobody is empowered to pull the plug,  
your observability stack is just a very expensive diary.

